    "body": "Update:\r\n\r\nOk its related to the specific mouse model, after changing the code, that it only enumerates for ledger vendor id the error does not occur anymore.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfor _, info := range hid.Enumerate(0x2c97, 0) { // Can't enumerate directly, one valid ID is the 0 wildcard\r\n```\r\n\r\nI will do more testings, also with my ledger nano s, if it still works with that change.\r\nI'm not sure if this is a change/fix you guys as the authors like but since its a \"ledger_hub\", which creates \"ledger_wallets\" i guess restricting the enumeration to only the ledger vendor id should be ok.\r\n",
